# grapher_calcmenu_implicit_smoke.numos — Phase 10G. Calculate menu on an
# implicit contour.
#
# Commits "x^2+y^2=9" (a circle), enters Trace, and presses ENTER to open the
# Calculate menu. Proves Phase 10G's adaptive menu: ENTER now opens on ANY
# traceable curve (not just y=f(x)). For a single implicit contour the menu greys
# Find Root / Find Minimum / Find Maximum / Find Intersection / Calculate Integral
# (all single-valued y=f(x) concepts, or needing a 2nd curve) and leaves only
# "Draw Tangent" selectable — so the calculator never offers a calculation that
# would fabricate a wrong result on a curve it isn't defined for.
#
# Flow (src/apps/GrapherApp.cpp): handleGraphTrace ENTER -> openCalcMenu ->
# calcItemEnabled(kind,item) builds the enable mask -> restyleCalcMenu greys the
# disabled rows and starts the cursor on the first enabled item (Draw Tangent).
#
# Warning-only: screenshot, NO golden, NOT CI-gated (absent from the
# generate-emulator-candidates CANDIDATES list and every emulator-build.yml step).
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/grapher_calcmenu_implicit_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 1000 --screenshot out/grapher_calcmenu_implicit_smoke.ppm --quiet
log "grapher_calcmenu_implicit: start"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
# down -> Add row; enter -> edit slot 0; type "x^2+y^2=9" (right exits each exponent).
key down
key enter
key x
key ^
key 2
key right
key +
key y
key ^
key 2
key right
key =
key 9
key enter
wait 60
# Phase 10G: the Graph tab opens directly in a centred Trace for an implicit
# equation; zoom once so the circle is large, then ENTER opens the Calculate menu.
key graph
wait 60
key zoom
wait 40
key enter
wait 80
screenshot out/grapher_calcmenu_implicit_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "grapher_calcmenu_implicit: menu open, only Draw Tangent enabled"
